<div id="banner">
	<h1>Books Consume Life</h1>
</div>

<div class="content">
<p>I&#8217;m the kind of crazy web-head who finds replacing paper book marks by storing current page numbers on a remote web-accessible-server I don&#8217;t control but can get my data out of via XML appealing. That&#8217;s probably why I like <a href="http://allconsuming.net/">All Consuming</a> so much.</p>

<p>All Consuming is the weblogger&#8217;s book portal. It keeps track of the most mentioned books, let&#8217;s you post commentary on books via TrackBack and has a web/db set-up which lets you keep track of which books you&#8217;ve purchased, read and are reading, with export feeds in XML and RSS.</p>

<p>For now I&#8217;ll point you to the page for <a href="http://allconsuming.net/item.cgi?id=068486875X">Emergence</a>, the book I read this weekend.</p>

<p class="posted">posted September 01, 2002 02:48 PM (<a class="category" href="http://www.aaronsw.com/weblog/cat_technology">Technology</a>)  <a href="000553" rel="bookmark">#</a></p>
</div>

